*** To register, fill out Docs/SREReg.TXT and send it in.øø ***

What we do is send you a registration code that you type into SRE and it
will register itself.  We do not create a 'registered version' or send you
a disk.  The reason?  In many games, you can register one version and the
next version requires a new fee for upgrade.  For SRE, you get the numbers
that work in ALL versions of SRE.  That way, you will be able to get all
future versions for free from local BBSes.

NOTE: We do not register this game under handles (for various reasons).
      If you wish to see where your name will appear, run SRE SYSOP
      and choose "Registered Version".

Non-US persons:  Checks / money orders must be US funds from a U.S. bank.
                 Otherwise, send US cash or an international money order.
                 (in Canada, the Post Office can issue Money Orders in
                 U.S. funds.)  If you are in Canada, you may want to contact
                 Hardy Rosenke (see Docs/Distrib.TXT) to see if he can help
                 in converting Canadian funds to U.S. funds.

                 You may also wish to get together with other sysops in
                 your area to register together; you will save on the
                 currency conversion charges and also on postage.  I
                 will send the registrations to each person separately.

Make out checks or money orders to "Amit J. Patel".  Sorry, NO credit card
orders.  Expect 3-4 weeks to receive your numbers.  We try to handle
everything as fast as possible, but sometimes it just doesn't get done
soon enough.  Also, I have lots of homework!!!

