  SOURCE CODE TO SRE / DOOR PROGRAMMING KIT
ÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄ

      It is our policy not to distribute any source code for our games.
      In the future we may release 'toolkits' for programmers to write their
      own games.  We are working on an easy-to-use 'most natural' toolkit
      which will require a minimal amount of learning for programmers.
      For example, Turbo Pascal users would still use Writeln, not S_WRITE,
      I_WRITE, L_WRITE, and other strange procedures that other door driver
      kits use.  Turbo C++ users use 'kout <<' instead of 'cout <<'
      (or #define cout kout), so that very little modification has to be
      made to a screen program to make it a modem program.  The toolkits
      support COM1 - COM4 in TP, or COM1 - COM8 in TC++, and will be easily
      extendible.  (And they'll come with source.)

      There is an early version of the Turbo C++ routines available on our
      board; if you want the latest version, please write a letter to me
      and I will send you a disk with all the routines.

